00:01:03.150 --> 00:01:04.320
Talk to me about resilience.

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:07.710
- It's something I think we in Finland

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:09.000
know, knows something about.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:11.190
Actually, it's one of our key words.

00:01:11.190 --> 00:01:16.190
It's cso, which is
resilience, perseverance,

00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:18.450
grit, stamina.

00:01:18.450 --> 00:01:21.360
So you basically, you never
give up, you just have

00:01:21.360 --> 00:01:24.120
to keep on pushing and grinding
through the tough stuff.

00:01:24.120 --> 00:01:26.880
And I think a lot of fins have

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:28.590
that ingrained into the system

00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:30.660
because remember, we're a poor country.

00:01:30.660 --> 00:01:33.600
You know, first we were
under Sweden for 700 years,

00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.030
then under Russia for a
little bit over a hundred.

00:01:36.030 --> 00:01:38.910
And when we gained independence in 1917,

00:01:38.910 --> 00:01:41.460
we were basically a
poor developing country.

00:01:41.460 --> 00:01:44.790
And I think then this sort of
idea of resilience, let's try

00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:48.030
to overcome, let's work hard,
came very much a part of,

00:01:48.030 --> 00:01:49.080
of finished DNA

00:01:49.080 --> 00:01:51.360
and i I, I think I'm still
part of that generation.

